      "content": "Garlic does contain compounds that can inhibit blood clotting, but the evidence supporting its use as a natural alternative to warfarin is limited and inconclusive. While some studies suggest that garlic may help lower the risk of heart disease and blood clots, these findings do not necessarily translate to a safe and effective substitute for warfarin in managing your specific condition. \r\n\r\nAdditionally, taking high doses of garlic supplements can interact with other medications, including warfarin, and may cause adverse effects such as stomach upset, bleeding, and interactions with iron supplements.",
